Infotexts.ntg.description.cyberkidney:
A cybernetic kidney replacement. Embrace the certainty of steel!
\nAvailable as a more affordable Cyber-augmented Kidney (half meat, half silicon) crafted from an extracted Kidney, or the twice as effective fully-synthetic Cyberkidney. Can be repaired during surgery with a screwdriver.
\nAdvantages of Cyberkidneys:
- You only need one;
- Improves resistance to Blood Loss and Bleeding;
- Switches blood type to C+, which can accept every single blood type;
- Improves resistance to Kidney Damage
\nDisadvantages of Cyberkidneys:
- Can periodically experience fits of Cyberpsychosis (regular psychosis), which can be avoided by reducing your Immunity in any way; such as the very affordable Immunosuppressant Inhaler;
- C+ Blood cannot be given to people without C+ blood as well;
- Vulnerable to EMPs
\nHow to add to a patient:
First, open up the torso as a typical surgery with retracted skin and remove the current kidneys. Then, place the Cyberkidney in instead and end the surgery; you only need one!. The Mechanical skill requirement is 60, while the Medical is 70.
\nHow to remove from a patient:
Re-open the torso and apply the Multipurpose Scalpel set to Adaptive Organ Extraction mode twice, removing the organ. Be sure to replace it!
